{"id":961,"date":"2022-01-30T16:56:00","date_gmt":"2022-01-30T16:56:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=961"},"modified":"2022-01-28T11:48:31","modified_gmt":"2022-01-28T11:48:31","slug":"list-create-delete-partitions-on-mbr-and-gpt-disks","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=961","title":{"rendered":"List, create, delete partitions on MBR and GPT disks"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>We are going to do a lot of disk management related tasks and to do that we need to add a few disks into our system. If you are using VirtualBox or any other hypervisor, this should be peace of an PI.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"adding-disks-to-the-system\">Adding disks to the system<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>First power off your VM and go to its settings. Go to the storage category and left-click on the add disk icon.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"196\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-208.png?resize=640%2C196&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-965\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-208.png?w=653&amp;ssl=1 653w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-208.png?resize=300%2C92&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-208.png?resize=24%2C7&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-208.png?resize=36%2C11&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-208.png?resize=48%2C15&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on create, choose VDI and dynamically allocated disk and choose let&#8217;s say 5G.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"236\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-207.png?resize=640%2C236&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-964\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-207.png?w=663&amp;ssl=1 663w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-207.png?resize=300%2C110&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-207.png?resize=24%2C9&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-207.png?resize=36%2C13&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-207.png?resize=48%2C18&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Repeat process at least 3x times, so we have enough disk to play with. In the end, it should look like this. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"519\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-209.png?resize=640%2C519&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-966\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-209.png?w=646&amp;ssl=1 646w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-209.png?resize=300%2C243&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-209.png?resize=24%2C19&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-209.png?resize=36%2C29&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-209.png?resize=48%2C39&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"listing-the-partitions\">Listing the partitions<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For listing, we almost always use lsblk command aka list blocks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">lsblk <\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"500\" height=\"212\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-210.png?resize=500%2C212&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-967\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-210.png?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-210.png?resize=300%2C127&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-210.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-210.png?resize=36%2C15&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-210.png?resize=48%2C20&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"mbr-vs-gpt-8e-vs-83\">MBR vs GPT | 8e vs 83<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before continuing, I feel like you should know about the difference between the two.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p><strong>MBR<\/strong> is the standard partitioning scheme that&#8217;s been used on hard disks since the PC first came out. It supports 4 primary partitions per hard drive, and a maximum partition size of 2TB.<\/p><p><strong>GPT<\/strong> disks are new, and are readable only by Windows Server 2003 SP1, Windows Vista (all versions), and Windows XP x64 Edition. The GPT disk itself can support a volume up to 2<sup>64<\/sup> blocks in length. (For 512-byte blocks, this is 9.44 ZB &#8211; zettabytes. 1 ZB is 1 billion terabytes). It can also support theoretically unlimited partitions.<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Basically, GPT is a newer version of partitioning which is used more and more nowadays because of it&#8217;s support for disks larger than 2TB.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>They both used different tools and commands for their configuration.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>fdisk for the old way called <strong>MBR<\/strong> ( Master Boot Record Partition)<\/li><li>gdisk for the modern way called <strong>GPT<\/strong> ( GUID Partition Table)<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>And the another thing you should know is the difference in the partition type 8e vs 83 aka LVM vs Linux<a href=\"https:\/\/serverfault.com\/posts\/519848\/timeline\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>The partition type byte is just that, a single byte in the Partition Table that holds a value that&nbsp;<em>should<\/em>&nbsp;relate to the file system inside the associated partition. It&#8217;s really just a hint of what methods the OS should try when attempting to read\/mount the partition. If you didn&#8217;t have this the system would need to try to read the partition using a number of types &#8211; and obviously it could get this wrong.<\/p><p>An analogy would be that if I read a phone number and it started with 001 or 044 I could start the conversion in English with a good chance of being understood from the start &#8211; it could be wrong but there&#8217;s a good chance it would be ok. If it said 033 then I could assume that starting in French would be a good idea, 039 and I could try Italian first &#8211; and so on. Basically it&#8217;s a strong-indicator, but only that &#8211; it can be wrong, of the underlying file system&#8217;s type.<\/p><p>As to what the actual difference is between those two options &#8211; well that could go on to be a very long answer but essentially LVM deals with extents and has multiple additional layers of abstraction that clearly need to be considered during boot &#8211; whereas the standard Linux Partition Type should be a lot more straightforward than LVM for the OS to deal with. Either way the booting kernel would benefit from knowing what to try first.<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>What&#8217;s the real benefit, you may ask?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>LVM is the Logical Volume Manager. It allows you to do things like group several physical disks together to appear as a single logical disk (similar to but not the same as raid0).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The only real advantage to using LVM with a single disk is snapshots.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/lh4.googleusercontent.com\/m2ojEMHs-NA2xSTamxtL1bc3F25aLCbRsR0uGvrCBV3Z9Q4Ibipl-PDRQqUGEZDqaBl9uoaIrERi3OJRv6TTY--PDercyvpU_GvCm3Mh_9wf4t2Cs6wNHTr0ftvjIYgwaBcIdH0T\" width=\"602\" height=\"343\"><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"creating-the-partitions\">Creating the partitions <\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"mbr\">MBR<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>To create a new partition on MBR we will use a tool called fdisk<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">fdisk \/dev\/sdb<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Press n for new partition<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press f for primary<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press enter for default partition number<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press enter for default sector range<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press enter to use all the space from disk<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can type t for type and choose: Linux 83 (which is default) or LVM 8e<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press w to write <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"333\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-211.png?resize=640%2C333&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-968\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-211.png?w=703&amp;ssl=1 703w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-211.png?resize=300%2C156&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-211.png?resize=24%2C12&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-211.png?resize=36%2C19&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-211.png?resize=48%2C25&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"594\" height=\"171\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-212.png?resize=594%2C171&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-969\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-212.png?w=594&amp;ssl=1 594w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-212.png?resize=300%2C86&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-212.png?resize=24%2C7&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-212.png?resize=36%2C10&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-212.png?resize=48%2C14&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"516\" height=\"199\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-213.png?resize=516%2C199&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-970\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-213.png?w=516&amp;ssl=1 516w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-213.png?resize=300%2C116&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-213.png?resize=24%2C9&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-213.png?resize=36%2C14&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-213.png?resize=48%2C19&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 516px) 100vw, 516px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"gpt\">GPT<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>For GPT we use gdisk which was created to be equivalent to fdisk but for GPT partitioning<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">gdisk \/dev\/vdc<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Press n for new partition<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press enter for default partition number<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press enter for default First sector starting range<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Type a size: +2G<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\/\/let&#8217;s try not to use whole filesystem this time<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Type in Hex code for filesystem if you dont want default Linux one: 8e00 for Linux LVM<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\/\/You can type L to list all the file system choices, they are the same as in the fdisk tool but with some zeroes at the end<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press w to write <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"341\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-214.png?resize=640%2C341&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-972\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-214.png?w=709&amp;ssl=1 709w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-214.png?resize=300%2C160&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-214.png?resize=24%2C13&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-214.png?resize=36%2C19&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-214.png?resize=48%2C26&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"497\" height=\"212\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-215.png?resize=497%2C212&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-973\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-215.png?w=497&amp;ssl=1 497w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-215.png?resize=300%2C128&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-215.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-215.png?resize=36%2C15&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-215.png?resize=48%2C20&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 497px) 100vw, 497px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"deleting-the-partitions\">Deleting the partitions<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"mbr-1\">MBR<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">fdisk \/dev\/sdb<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Press d for delete<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press w to write<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"293\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-217.png?resize=640%2C293&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-976\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-217.png?w=668&amp;ssl=1 668w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-217.png?resize=300%2C137&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-217.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-217.png?resize=36%2C16&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-217.png?resize=48%2C22&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"470\" height=\"216\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-218.png?resize=470%2C216&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-977\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-218.png?w=470&amp;ssl=1 470w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-218.png?resize=300%2C138&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-218.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-218.png?resize=36%2C17&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-218.png?resize=48%2C22&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 470px) 100vw, 470px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"gpt-1\">GPT<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre id=\"deleting-the-partitions\" class=\"wp-block-preformatted\"> gdisk \/dev\/sdc<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Press d for delete<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press w for write<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"363\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-219.png?resize=640%2C363&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-978\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-219.png?w=725&amp;ssl=1 725w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-219.png?resize=300%2C170&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-219.png?resize=24%2C14&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-219.png?resize=36%2C20&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-219.png?resize=48%2C27&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"465\" height=\"200\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-220.png?resize=465%2C200&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-979\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-220.png?w=465&amp;ssl=1 465w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-220.png?resize=300%2C129&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-220.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-220.png?resize=36%2C15&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content